other_tests.findings: Gallbladder wall is thick and edematous, measuring 6 mm, with fat stranding in the surrounding tissue. No focal lesions are seen in the liver. The pancreas is atrophic. There is a biliary stent in place. No free fluid or free air. Large and small bowel appear within normal limits. Two well-circumscribed lytic lesions within the L4 vertebral body adjacent to the superior endplate with surrounding sclerosis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The lytic lesions within the L4 vertebral body and elongated lucent lesion along the inferior endplate of L3 vertebral body were seen again, similar in appearance to prior CT.

other_tests.findings: Gallstones, GB wall thickening, and a sonographic Murphy's sign.
